Dear Splynx administrator,
<br>
this section is used for creating templates for any purposes you require. <br>
You may use existing templates, modify them or create some of your own: invoices, payment receipts, messages to customers and teams, any information needed to display can be added through editing system.
<br><br>

You can use a great number of variables in templates:
For example,  to get customer name please use <b>{{ customer.name }}</b>, <br>
to display customer login - <b>{{ customer.login }}</b>.<br>
Customer password can be added through <b>{{ customer.password }} </b> option.<br>
Status of current customer is added using variable <b>{{ customer.status }}</b>.<br>
Payment amount can be added using this variable - <b> {{ payment.amount }} </b>.<br>
In case you need to add invoice number, please use - <b>{{ payment.invoice_id }} </b>. <br>
<br>
To get payment and invoice variables working you should use them in PDF or reminders and notification section of the system,
<br>
<br>
While editing template, please refer to Placeholders tab of editing window where you can add necessary variable to template you are currently modifying by simply clicking on necessary item.
<br>
